    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-08-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-08-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="411"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d411">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">White</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-08-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 22, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1391.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your No. 2024, of the 5th instant, relating” to
                    the defilement of the coat of arms of the United States at the consulate in
                    Bamberg, has been received.</p>
                <p>The Department is gratified at the friendly spirit shown by the Government of
                    Germany in regretting the incident and in bringing it about that the new coat of
                    arms will be put in place in a solemn manner.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
